briefdescription.para: Returns the GDAL driver name for a specified file extension.

detaileddescription.para: E.g. the driver name for the ".tif" extension is "GTiff". If no suitable drivers are found then an empty string is returned.
Note that this method works for all GDAL drivers, including those without create support (and which are not supported by QgsRasterFileWriter).

briefdescription.para: Returns a list of known file extensions for the given GDAL driver format.

detaileddescription.para: If no matching format driver is found an empty list will be returned.
Note that this method works for all GDAL drivers, including those without create support (and which are not supported by QgsRasterFileWriter).

briefdescription.para: Creates a filter for an GDAL driver key.
Returns a list or pairs, with format filter string as first element and GDAL format key as second element.

detaileddescription.para: Relies on GDAL_DMD_EXTENSIONS metadata, if it is empty corresponding driver will be skipped even if supported.
The options argument can be used to control the sorting and filtering of returned formats.
